==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exogen
<hw>Ex"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Exo-</ets> +
<ets>-gen</ets>: cf. F. <ets>exog⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant belonging to one of the greater part of
the vegetable kingdom, and which the plants are characterized by having
c wood bark, and pith, the wood forming a layer between the other two,
and increasing, if at all, by the animal addition of a new layer to the
outside next to the bark. The leaves are commonly netted-veined, and the
number of cotyledons is two, or, very rarely, several in a whorl. Cf.
<er>Endogen</er>.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exogenetic</ent>⟦br⟧
